decision_conditions:
Condition : 7 - No development (excluding demolition, archaeological investigations, ground conditions investigations and intrusive site surveys and other enabling works, site clearance, soil storage, remedial work in respect of any contamination or other adverse ground conditions, diversion of culvert, erection of any temporary means of enclosure and land raising) shall take place above ground until details and samples of all facing materials are submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The samples and details shall include: 
- cladding materials (including system specifications/details and on-site samples with a minimum one-storey equivalent mock-up for the external facade); 
- window treatment (including sections/reveals and on-site sample panel);  
- obscure glazing details (where relevant); 
- balustrading treatment including sections (where relevant); 
- any other materials/details to be used including extract vents, boiler flues, etc.  
The development shall then be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained as such thereafter.

Condition : 11 - Prior to the completion of the frame of the building, details of both hard and soft landscape works for that phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The works shall then be carried out as approved.  
The detailed landscaping scheme shall include:  
- soft planting: including any grass and turf areas, trees, planters, shrub and herbaceous areas including details of species, sizes, numbers/densities and sections of landscaped areas; 
- a 'Tree Planting Statement' providing full details, locations, specifications and construction methods for all purpose-built tree pits and associated above ground features, including specifications for tree protection and a stated volume of suitable growing medium to facilitate and promote the healthy development of the proposed trees, ensuring each tree has a soil volume equivalent of 0.6 times its canopy area at maturity; 
- hard landscaping: including ground surfaces, kerbs, edges, ridge and flexible paving, furniture, steps, refuse disposal points and if applicable synthetic surfaces for both ground level and roof terrace level); 
- fences and walls and any other boundary treatments;  
- any signage (Legible London) and information boards;  
- brown (biodiversity) roofs/green walls (where relevant); 
- any CCTV equipment;
- any external lighting; and 
- any other landscaping feature(s) forming part of the scheme.  
The submission shall include a management programme for the lifetime of the development, which shall include: long term design objectives, management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all hard and soft landscape areas, and details of any temporary landscaping (including boundary treatment) to be provided and management thereof. All landscaping comprised in the approved details shall be carried out during the first planting and seeding seasons following completion of construction works. Any trees or shrubs planted (including any such replacements) which d
